FBIS3-14973 "drsov041cc_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-041 Document Type:Daily Report 2 March 1994 INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS Samsonov Sees `Growing Interest' in Defense Cooperation PM0103144794 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 1 Mar 94 p 1 PM0103144794 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Gennadiy Miranovich report: "Council of CIS Defense Ministers Acquires New Quality"] [Text] The Council of CIS Defense Ministers has acquired a new quality. And Colonel General Viktor Samsonov, chief of the Staff for Coordinating Military Cooperation, commented that this does not only stem from the Statute on the Council of Commonwealth Defense Ministers that has been adopted. As you know, in connection with a number of new states subscribing to the Treaty on Collective Security this body, which previously also performed political functions, is now the Collective Security Council's main consultative body on military questions. Commenting on the results of the latest session of the Council of Defense Ministers 24-25 February, Col. Gen. Samsonov also pointed to the growing interest among the independent states' military departments in strengthening defense cooperation.
